{
 "id": "karadun",
 "name": "Karadun — Glass Field",
 "world": "Karadun",
 "description": "Open glass with no natural cover except two melt-trenches that both lead to the console pole — one from the southwest, one from the northeast. Both sides know it. That's the map.",
 "ambientRegister": "Pale amber-white glass, thin washed-out sky, a tonal hum off the pole.",
 "designRationale": "Open maps suit deny/rout objectives, but bare-open is boring traversal — so the two covered approaches are mirrored and collide at the pole ring: a designed collision point. Rock clusters cut flank lanes without ever one-tiling. The pole ring's cover faces outward: it rewards arriving first.",
